{"id": 329, "title": "Ticket #329: Condor-C over-reports RemoteWallClockTime", "description": "<blockquote>\nI noticed that when Condor-C jobs finish, on the submit side, the <code>RemoteWallClockTime</code> stored in the job <code>ClassAd</code> is about double what it should be.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2015-Apr-16 11:18:12 by jfrey:</em> <br/>\n\nThis is because the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=CondorJob\" title=\"Condor Job\">CondorJob</a></span> object in the gridmanager propagates the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=RemoteWallClockTime\" title=\"Remote Wall Clock Time\">RemoteWallClockTime</a></span> value from the remote job ad into the local job ad in the schedd. Then, when the job completes, BaseJob::UpdateRuntimeStats() adds its own calculation of how long the job's been running (calculated from <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ShadowBday\" title=\"Shadow Bday\">ShadowBday</a></span> in the local ad).\n\n<p>We should use BaseJob::calcRuntimeStats to eliminate this double-counting of runtime.</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=5007\" title=\"Condor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts\">#5007</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nCondor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jun-01 13:15</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=44926\">[44926]</a></span>: minor 8.2.9 version history item edit <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=329\" title=\"Condor-C over-reports RemoteWallClockTime\">#329</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=5007\" title=\"Condor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts\">#5007</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-30 16:44</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=44772\">[44772]</a></span>: Docs for Condor-C runtime double-count bug fix. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=329\" title=\"Condor-C over-reports RemoteWallClockTime\">#329</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=5007\" title=\"Condor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts\">#5007</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-30 16:44</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=44771\">[44771]</a></span>: Don't double count the runtime of Condor-C jobs. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=329\" title=\"Condor-C over-reports RemoteWallClockTime\">#329</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=5007\" title=\"Condor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts\">#5007</a></span> Instead, take all runtime attributes (including <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ShadowBday\" title=\"Shadow Bday\">ShadowBday</a></span>) from the remote schedd and don't modify them in the gridmanager.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2015-May-14 16:32", "status": "resolved", 